doc.after: The Code of Federal Regulations CFR is the codification of the general and permanent rules and regulations sometimes called administrative law published in the Federal Register by the executive departments and agencies of the federal government of the United States The CFR is divided into 50 titles that represent broad areas subject to federal regulation
